Theory Summary

Learned about:

Lists, Tuples, Sets, Dictionaries: storing and organizing data.

Functions & Lambda Functions: modularize code.

Recursion: functions calling themselves.

List Comprehension: concise looping for transformations.
# Calculate average temperature from user input
temps = []
n = int(input("Enter number of days: "))

for i in range(n):
    t = float(input(f"Enter temperature for day {i+1}: "))
    temps.append(t)

avg_temp = sum(temps) / len(temps)
print(f"Average Temperature: {avg_temp:.2f}Â°C")
